n, and no global abort is triggered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior is about semantic faithfulness of generated narrative to input values, which depends on real model judgment/output quality (LLM-DEP yes; deterministic fixture would mask real failures per deterministic-assertion trap). Not primarily OS/network/subprocess behavior. Rejected Workflow because this behavior targets one generation decision, not multiple agentic decisions chained in sequence (MULTI-STEP no).","test_description":"Provide controlled input datasets with known key values to the real summary-generation model and assert output preserves critical facts/figures (with tolerance rubric for wording variation) across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external delivery path and inbox receipt (REAL-INFRA yes: real HTTP/API or SMTP + mailbox). In-process mocks can hide transport/auth/routing/inbox-integration failures (MOCK-HIDE yes). Although pipeline may include summary generation, this behavior’s pass/fail is delivery of complete report, not model output quality, so Agentic is not strictly required as minimum here.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled/report pipeline against reachable test instances of the three data sources and a real test email service/mailbox; assert one delivered email arrives in the configured inbox with expected report structure/content